n")\n- In `sw_chat_input_bar.dart`, the TextField uses `onSubmitted` but not `on
Changed`. The listener is added via `_effectiveController.addListener(_onTextCha
nged)`, which is correct for Maestro compatibility.\n- However, there\'s no focu
s listener to auto-select text on focus for Maestro inputText. But wait, this is
a chat input field - it\'s typically empty when focused, so auto-select may not 
be as critical. The spec says "获得焦点时自动全选旧内容" for fields that may hav
e old content.\n\nLet me check more critical issues:\n1. `chat_page.dart` uses `
GestureDetector(onTapDown: ...)` for back button and retry - good for Maestro\n2
. The `chat_page.dart` marks as read on `MessagesLoaded && state.isInitialLoad`.
But what if the user receives new messages while in the chat? It doesn\'t auto-m
ark those as read. That\'s actually probably correct behavior - you only mark as
read when you open or maybe when you scroll. But the PRD says "When Bob opens th
e conversation, all unread messages from Alice should be marked as read". It doe
sn\'t say auto-mark on new message arrival.\n\nLet me look at more critical issu
es:\n- In `im_bloc.dart`, `_onSendMessage` sets `sequenceId: -1` for temp messag
es, and when ack comes back it updates to the real sequenceId. That\'s good.\n- 
In `im.service.ts`, `getMessages` returns messages in ascending order after reve
rsing. But the `next_cursor` is set to `messages[0].sequence_id` which is the ol
dest message in the returned batch (since it was reversed). Wait - `messages.rev
erse()` makes the first element the oldest. So `next_cursor = messages[0].sequen
ce_id` would be the oldest sequence_id. But for pagination going backwards, you 
want the cursor to be the oldest message so next time you query `sequence_id < c
ursor`. Let me trace through:\n  - QueryBuilder orders by `sequence_id DESC`, ta
kes `parsedLimit + 1`\n  - Results are newest first. If hasMore, slice to parsed
Limit (still newest first)\n  - Then `messages.reverse()` makes them oldest firs
t for display\n  - `nextCursor = hasMore && messages.length > 0 ? String(message
s[0].sequence_id) : null`\n  - messages[0] after reverse is the OLDEST message i
n this batch\n  - Next query uses `cursor` with `sequence_id < :cursor`\n  - So 
yes, this is correct - you query for messages older than the oldest one currentl
y loaded.\n\nWait, but there\'s a subtle bug. If `messages.length == 0`, nextCur
sor is null (protected by `messages.length > 0`). But what about when `hasMore` 
is false? Then nextCursor is null. That seems correct.\n\nActually wait - `messa
ges` after reverse: if hasMore was true, results had parsedLimit+1 items, slice 
to parsedLimit, then reverse. So messages[0] is the oldest of the parsedLimit it
ems. The next query will fetch items with sequence_id < that, which is correct.\
n\nBut what about the initial load? The first load gets the newest 20 messages, 
