ed_at DESC`\n- Then it fetches conversations by `In(conversationIds)` - this los
es ordering!\n- The `pageParticipants.map(...)` uses `pageParticipants` order to
build items, but `conversationMap.get()` just gets the conversation. The order i
s preserved by `pageParticipants.map`. That\'s fine.\n- `lastMessages` uses nati
ve SQL with `IN (?)` and passes `[conversationIds]` - this is the mysql2 array t
rap mentioned in db.md! mysql2 will NOT expand `IN (?)` to multiple placeholders
. It will serialize the array as a comma-separated string, which may cause incor
rect query behavior.\n\nWait, this is a MAJOR issue! Let me re-read db.md:\n> 陷
阱 6：IN (?) 传入数组时 mysql2 不会自动展开为 IN (?, ?, ?)\n\nAnd in im.service.
ts line 404-414:\n```typescript\nconst lastMessages = await this.dataSource.quer
y(\n  `\n  SELECT m.* FROM messages m\n  INNER JOIN (\n    SELECT conversation_i
d, MAX(sequence_id) as max_seq\n    FROM messages\n    WHERE conversation_id IN 
(?)\n    GROUP BY conversation_id\n  ) latest ON m.conversation_id = latest.conv
ersation_id AND m.sequence_id = latest.max_seq\n`,\n  [conversationIds],\n);\n``
`\n\nThis is a BUG! The `conversationIds` is an array. In mysql2, `IN (?)` with 
an array parameter will serialize it as `IN (\'id1,id2,id3\')` - a single string
