ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='The OpenAPI contract also allows `system` type in `SendMessageRequest
`. So the contract itself has the same bug as the DTO. This means fixing the DTO
alone would create an inconsistency with the OpenAPI contract. Both need to be u
pdated.\n\nAlso, I notice `MessageDto.status` enum in OpenAPI is `[sent, read]`,
which matches the DB. Good.\n\nLet me now write the review report. I have enough
evidence.\n\nSummary of issues to include:\n\n**Blocking:**\n1. `im.service.ts:4
04-414` - Native SQL `IN (?)` with array parameter. mysql2 doesn\'t expand array
s. Breaks conversation list last message retrieval.\n   - Fix: Use manual placeh
older expansion or QueryBuilder.\n   - Evidence: `docs/design-docs/db.md` line 1
87-207 (陷阱 6)\n\n2. `send-message.dto.ts:19` and `im.service.ts:70-84` - Allow
s `type: "system"` in user-facing send message API. Users can spoof system messa
ges.\n   - Fix: Remove `"system"` from `@IsIn` in DTO and OpenAPI contract, add 
service guard.\n   - Evidence: PRD says system messages are auto-inserted by bac
kend, not sent by users.\n\n**Major:**\n3. `im_bloc.dart:565-569` + `match_list_
page.dart:41-54` - Double API fetch on real-time updates. `ImBloc` fetches conve
rsations on socket update, then `MatchListPage` triggers `ConversationListCubit`
to fetch again.\n   - Fix: Have `ImBloc` emit a lightweight refresh signal inste
ad of re-fetching, or remove redundant fetch from `ImBloc`.\n\n4. `send-message.
dto.ts:14-17` - `content` lacks `@IsString()` validation for non-text messages. 
`ValidateIf` skips all validation for image/system types.\n   - Fix: Add `@IsStr
ing()` unconditionally (before `@ValidateIf` or alongside it).\n\n**Minor:**\n5.
`apps/api/src/database/entities/message.entity.ts` and migration `20250426000000
-CreateImTables.ts` - `messages` table lacks `updated_at` column. db.md requires
every table to have both `created_at` and `updated_at`.\n   - Fix: Add `updated_
at` column to entity and migration.\n\nLet me double-check if there are any othe
r issues I should mention.\n\nActually, looking at `im.gateway.ts`, the `emitCon
versationUpdated` method emits to both sender and receiver rooms. But in `handle
SendMessage`, it also emits `message:receive` to the receiver and `message:ack`/
`message:delivered` to the sender. Then it calls `emitConversationUpdated` which
emits `conversation:updated` to BOTH. This means the sender gets TWO events for 
their own message: `message:ack` (or `message:delivered`) AND `conversation:upda
ted`. Is this redundant?\n\nFor the sender:\n- `message:ack` confirms the messag
e was saved\n- `message:delivered` confirms the receiver is online\n- `conversat
ion:updated` tells the sender to refresh their conversation list\n\nThese are ac
tually different purposes. The conversation list needs to know about the new mes
sage to update the last message preview. So `conversation:updated` is needed for
the sender too. This is fine.\n\nFor the receiver:\n- `message:receive` delivers
the actual message\n- `conversation:updated` tells them to refresh the conversat
ion list\n\nIf the receiver is currently in the chat page, `message:receive` add
s the message to the chat. `conversation:updated` would trigger `ConversationLis
tCubit.fetchConversations()` if they\'re on the match list page. If they\'re in 
